ecZ6W_93LCv_6Nqk-7fEl9SgYwNCl7hwY_3X0aUA0yEnp2hzwos1RQy9dD5tQPj0dcpvCK7XtfKx8n9e8pesvOnX9z_Xm7kexL8nKJJDYlQwsv90hDZqgBacy210_kl3VzeLAD0dYlcuLAyb3Q4e\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native image testing**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether tests for a native image will succeed, particularly regarding dynamic reflection and Class.forName. I wonder if getConstructor and newInstance require constructor metadata; if it's not registered, the native image might fail.\\n\\nThe repo appears to run tests with an agent that generates metadata, but I need to confirm if tests can run without it. It sounds like I should enhance test coverage to ensure dynamic access is correctly handled, though standard tests may still need metadata.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing reflection in tests**\\n\\nI’m considering that the existing tests may reflect correctly because of metadata generated during the build process. I want to inspect the harness without running it, though I'll need to design a minimal test that covers all dynamic calls.\\n\\nThe issue with create(Map) is it expects a Map, but invokes with RelInput, which seems impossible unless the object implements both. I could create a custom test class for the test package that meets this need. However, issues arise with Class.forName failing when trying to retrieve class in certain packages.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Class.forName in tests**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I can use Class.forName on a test class in a native environment. Since the test class is referenced directly by its name, it should be reachable. However, I'm concerned that using methods like getConstructor or newInstance may require reflection metadata.\\n\\nI think the dynamic access report will capture this, but the native image tests could fail if the agent configuration doesn't account for everything encountered. Typically, the TCK runs Java tests with an agent before native tests, which likely uses generated metadata, so I need to clarify that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_krRjtFADz52awyTEcapWUWjr|fc_052dc588b66f22cf0169f1819e6b70819cb07059dc86ea45fa", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"abstract class AbstractRelNode|interface RelNode|interface RelInput\" /home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/main/extracted/org/apache/calcite/rel -n"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"rg \\\"abstract class AbstractRelNode|interface RelNode|interface RelInput\\\" /home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/main/extracted/org/apache/calcite/rel -n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 486, "output": 1103, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25141, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777435023979, "responseId": "resp_052dc588b66f22cf0169f18190b7c8819c9eabc3d716b4e60a"}}
